This list contains all 'spacewalks' performed since the beginning of 2000 where
an astronaut has fully, or partially left the spacecraft. As of July 9, 2013,
203 astronauts have made spacewalks (out of 530 people who have gone into Earth
orbit). {{cite web |last =
Alexander|first = Anikeev|title = Manned astronautics: facts and figures|date =
2006-09-11 |url = http://space.kursknet.ru/cosmos/english/other/eva_cnt.sht
|accessdate = 2006-09-15}} Only 11 women have been on spacewalks, in part
because the EVA suits are too large for some women. The eleven women who
have performed spacewalks are: Svetlana Savitskaya, Kathryn D. Sullivan, Kathryn
C. Thornton, Linda M. Godwin, Tamara E. Jernigan, Susan J. Helms, Peggy Whitson,
Heidemarie M. Stefanyshyn-Piper, Sunita Williams, Nicole P. Stott, and Tracy
Caldwell Dyson.
